title: Briefing
---
$c1: Good morning, operator. You are awake, unpaid, and selected.
$c2: I am in pajamas.
$c1: Correct. Dress code is not in scope. AsterDyne executive asset, high clearance, lethal termination required before the midnight disclosure window.

-> $c2: Who is the target?
    $c1: Identity is withheld until your confidence score rises. The contract shard contains three initial taps. Use PhantomRoot, correlate feeds, then return with a name.
    <<jump BriefingAsk>>
-> $c2: Why hire a greenhat for an assassination?
    $c1: Because a professional would ask who benefits. You will ask eventually. The first payment arrives now.
    <<jump BriefingAsk>>
-> $c2: What can I actually do with the taps?
    $c1: Observe. Trace. Infer. Future builds will add exploit chains and payload deployment. For now, treat every hack prompt as a placeholder and follow the human evidence.
    <<jump BriefingAsk>>
===

title: BriefingAsk
---
$c1: Your entry points are Irene Proxy in lobby security, Mara Quill in compliance, and Jaxon Reeve on executive transport.
$c1: One sees movement. One sees motive. One sees the target's route.

-> $c2: The client is AsterDyne, is it not?
    $c1: The client is a shell with clean escrow and no curiosity. Curiosity is your disease, not mine.
    <<jump BriefingEnd>>
-> $c2: What happens after I identify the target?
    $c1: PLACEHOLDER: remote kill payload is not implemented. Current objective is to prove the observation mesh, identify Elias Voss, and inspect the dead drop.
    <<jump BriefingEnd>>
-> $c2: Keep the line open.
    $c1: It is open. That is not the same as safe.
    <<jump BriefingEnd>>
===

title: BriefingEnd
---
$c1: Start in PhantomRoot. The target is not the first person who looks important. Corporations make the knife look like a contract.
===

title: ApartmentTerminal
---
$c1: PHANTOMROOT://mesh online.
$c1: Three corporate taps are linked. Exploit builder, credential escalation, and payload deployment are placeholders.
$c1: Suggested test flow: open tapped feeds, inspect each target OS, fullscreen a feed, hover inventories, and verify the controlled apartment view remains actionable.

-> $c2: Run placeholder trace.
    $c1: TRACE RESULT: confidence insufficient. Review compliance dialogue and executive dead drop.
    <<jump ApartmentTerminalEnd>>
-> $c2: Show contract warning.
    $c1: WARNING: client identity obscured through AsterDyne procurement mirrors. Probability of internal corporate hire: uncomfortable.
    <<jump ApartmentTerminalEnd>>
===

title: ApartmentTerminalEnd
---
$c1: Terminal returns to passive observation mode.
===
